“'''老战士永不死'''”是[[英语|英语]]的口号，完整版是“老兵不死，只是逐漸凋零”。它是由士兵的民俗歌曲《Old Soldiers Never Die》中的一段组成的：老兵永不死 永不死，永不死， 老兵永不死 它们只是消失了。<ref>''Soldiers’ Songs and Slang of the Great War'', collected by Martin Pegler, {{ISBN|9781472804150}}, [https://books.google.com/books?id=M5aHCwAAQBAJ&pg=PT213 p. 123]; an update of [[John_Brophy_(writer)|John Brophy]] and [[Eric_Partridge|Eric Partridge]]'s ''Songs and Slang of the British Soldier'' (1930)</ref>这首歌本身就是英国陆军对福音歌曲《 Kind Thoughts Can Never Die》的模仿。<ref>{{Cite book|title=A dictionary of catch phrases : British and American, from the sixteenth century to the present day|last=1894-1979.|first=Partridge, Eric|date=1985|publisher=Routledge & Kegan Paul|others=Beale, Paul.|isbn=0203379950|edition=2nd.|location=London|oclc=57445962}}</ref>[[File:Douglas_MacArthur_speaking_at_Soldier_Field_HD-SN-99-03036.JPEG|thumb]]

